# scitex-session environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (gitignored) and edit values for your setup.
# CLI flags / decorator arguments always override env vars when both are
# given. Variables follow the SciTeX ecosystem convention:
# SCITEX_<MODULE>_<NAME>.
#
# Local state (per the SciTeX local-state convention) is read from:
#   ~/.scitex/session/               user-global config + cache
#   <proj-root>/.scitex/session/     project-local overrides (preferred)

# Redirect the whole session `_out` base off the script-adjacent default
# (`<script>_out/RUNNING/<ID>/`) to a resolved base such as node-local
# scratch — the HPC / SLURM-array inode-relief knob. When set, the RUNNING
# tree, the running->finished copytree, and any archive all stay under this
# directory and never touch a shared parallel filesystem (GPFS/Lustre).
# Unset (default) => byte-for-byte the legacy script-adjacent behaviour.
# See src/scitex_session/_skills/scitex-session/06_env-vars.md for details.
# SCITEX_SESSION_OUT_DIR=/path/to/node-local/scratch
